		<h2>About</h2>
		<p>I'm a programmer with talent in C++ and Java - I specialize in high-level class design, refactoring, and the controversial art of template metaprogramming. I develop <a href="http://www.LB-STuff.com/MMF2/Extensions/">software extensions</a> for the <a href="http://community.Clickteam.com/">Clickteam Community</a>, as well as <a href="https://github.com/LB--">my own projects</a> and group projects with the <a href="http://www.cplusplus.com">cplusplus.com</a> community.</p>
		<p>I'm still learning HTML and CSS, so as you can see this website is nowhere near as stunning as my code.</p>
		<p>I have a lot of files related to Clickteam Fusion 2.x <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/MMF2/">here</a>, such as examples, screenshots, etc.</p>
		<h2>Articles</h2>
		<p>I've written some articles on programming in my free time when I felt the passion to write. Here's a list:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>[programming] <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/gc.html">Garbage Collection is Wrong</a> - my understanding of GC and my advocation for RAII.</li>
			<li>[computing] <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/rebel.html">RebelOS - stop making assumptions</a> - blowing off steam that's been building up over the years.</li>
			<li>[C++] <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/alias.html">Variables are Aliases, not Objects!</a> - my recommended way of viewing variables and objects.</li>
			<li>[C++] <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/const.html">Const-Correctness is important!</a> - my reasons for supporting const-correctness.</li>
			<li>[philosophy] <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/combination.html">Useful Combinations</a> - my stance on DRM, software licensing, and more.</li>
			<li>[C++] <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/pointers.html">Pointers have little to no use</a> - my explanation for why I say pointers are useless.</li>
			<li>[programming] <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/optimization">Optimize as late as possible</a> - my recommendations on optimizing later rather than sooner.</li>
			<li>[programming] <a href="http://www.LB-Stuff.com/self-documenting.html">Write and Use Self-Documenting Code</a> - my explanation of self-documenting code and why you should use it.</li>
		</ul>
